<h1>Breakpoints</h1>
<pre><code class="language-scss">// Breakpoints
$small-range: (0px, 767px);
$medium-range: (768px, 1024px);
$large-range: (1025px, 1440px);
$xlarge-range: (1441px, 5000px);</code></pre>

<h3>Respond With Classes</h3>
<p>Apply classes to markup to control grid and column sizing at different breakpoints.</p>
<h4 class="docs__html">HTML</h4>

<pre><code class="language-html">&lt;div class="row"&gt;
    &lt;div class="small-12 medium-8 large-8 xlarge-7 columns"&gt;...&lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;div class="small-12 medium-4 large-4 xlarge-5 columns"&gt;...&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
</code></pre>

<h3>Respond With Sass</h3>
<p>Use these media queries in SASS. Choose between scaling or fixed ranges.<code>#{small-up}</code> would apply to <em>0px</em> and up until <code>#{medium-up}</code> overrides it. <code>#{small-only}</code> applies to a fixed range between <em>0px - 767px</em>.</p>
<h4 class="docs__html">SCSS</h4>

<pre><code class="language-scss">@media #{$small-up} {}              // 0px and up
@media #{$small-only} {}            // 0px - 767px
@media #{$medium-up} {}       		// 768px and up
@media #{$medium-only} {}     		// 768px - 1024px
@media #{$large-up} {}             	// 1024px and up
@media #{$large-only} {}           	// 1024px - 1440px
@media #{$xlarge-up} {}             // 1441px and up
@media #{$xlarge-only} {}           // 1441px - 5000px
</code></pre>
